    "He graduated from Yale University with a B. A. in 1957, serving in the United States Army Reserve between 1958 and 1964.": [],
    "He continued graduate work at Columbia University.": [],
    "In 1962 he was appointed assistant professor of classical art and archaeology at Yale University.": [
